HEADWORD: Arthrodynia
<hw>Ar`thro*dyn"i*a</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>'a`rqron</grk> joint + <grk>'ody`nh</grk> pain.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An affection characterized by pain in or about a
joint, not dependent upon structural disease.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

